		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_NOTIFICATION_EVENT_ASSYRIA_UE_CHOICE_5_S">
			<Text>{3_PlayerName} receives a Unique Event for {1_CivShortDescription}.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_NOTIFICATION_EVENT_ASSYRIA_UE_CHOICE_5">
			<Text>{3_PlayerName} uncovers an ancient superstructure, igniting renewed hindrance of ancient Assyrian beliefs.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_NOTIFICATION_EVENT_ASSYRIA_UE_CHOICE_6_S">
			<Text>{3_PlayerName} receives a Unique Event for {1_CivShortDescription}.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_NOTIFICATION_EVENT_ASSYRIA_UE_CHOICE_6">
			<Text>{3_PlayerName} forms an elite Paratrooper program from the daring and zealous.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_ASSYRIA_UE_DESCRIPTION">
			<Text>The Tablet of Destiny</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_ASSYRIA_UE_HELP">
			<Text>Blessings of Ashur be upon you every day of your life, Great One. Forgive me for interrupting your study, but something has arisen.[NEWLINE][NEWLINE]Something pertaining to The Tablet...</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_ASSYRIA_UE_HELP_CHOICE_1">
			<Text>Receive a Great Person of your choice.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_ASSYRIA_UE_HELP_CHOICE_2">
			<Text>Monuments produce +2 [ICON_PRODUCTION] Production. All eligible Units, as well as those produced in the next {4_Turns}, gain the Amphibious promotion.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_ASSYRIA_UE_HELP_CHOICE_3">
			<Text>Pay {2_InstantYield}. Temples produce +2 and Holy Sites produce +4 [ICON_RESEARCH] Science. Libraries produce +2 and Academies produce +4 [ICON_PEACE] Faith.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_ASSYRIA_UE_HELP_CHOICE_4">
			<Text>Each City receives a free Synagogue. However, settling the refugees causes 1 [ICON_HAPPINESS_2] Unhappiness in each City.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_ASSYRIA_UE_HELP_CHOICE_5">
			<Text>The discovery starts {4_Turns} of [COLOR_POSITIVE_TEXT]WLTKD[ENDCOLOR] in all Cities. Landmarks yield +5 to [ICON_RESEARCH] Science, [ICON_PEACE] Faith and [ICON_PRODUCTION] Production.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_ASSYRIA_UE_HELP_CHOICE_6">
			<Text>A Paratrooper is recruited in every City. All Recon Units gain the Wings of Valor Promotion.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_ASSYRIA_UE_DESCRIPTION_CHOICE_1">
			<Text>*An adventurer has found a piece of the Tablet*[NEWLINE]See that all hear of the handsome reward that was given for this relic!</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_ASSYRIA_UE_DESCRIPTION_CHOICE_2">
			<Text>*Our bravest hero crossed a body of running water to lay the killing blow on our enemy while he slept, just as it was foretold!*[NEWLINE]Let the evidence of our destiny be carved in every City of the Empire!</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_ASSYRIA_UE_DESCRIPTION_CHOICE_3">
			<Text>*The leading expert in ancient languages believes he can decipher our library of forgotten prophecies and record*[NEWLINE]If the location of more of the Tablet is hidden amongst these slates, I must know of it!</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_ASSYRIA_UE_DESCRIPTION_CHOICE_4">
			<Text>*Once our enemies, a tribe of heathens fleeing their conquerors begs you for asylum. Just as was promised!*[NEWLINE]This is the will of the Gods! We must fulfil the prophecy, and settle these people in our lands.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_ASSYRIA_UE_DESCRIPTION_CHOICE_5">
			<Text>*A recent excavation has uncovered a massive temple complex, lost to history.*[NEWLINE]Restore this shrine, and all others like it. When their homes are rebuilt, the gods will return. So it is written!</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_EVENT_ASSYRIA_UE_DESCRIPTION_CHOICE_6">
			<Text>*Technological advancement has enabled our soldiers to fall, winged, from the sky.*[NEWLINE]The arrows of Ashur bringing the vengeance of the sun... Let the call go out, now is the time to fulfil our destiny!</Text>
		</Row>
		
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_PROMOTION_UE_WINGED_VALOR">
			<Text>Wings of Valor</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_PROMOTION_UE_WINGED_VALOR_HELP">
			<Text>+25% [ICON_STRENGTH] Combat Strength vs. Wounded enemies. Can force enemies to retreat, and deals extra damage if they cannot.</Text>
		</Row>
	</Language_en_US>
